channel.title: (W.I.P)Custom acoustic guitar(all prims)
channel.description:
here recently my grandfather past away and on his will he left me some items and one of these items was an OLD kent guitar so i made this model in his honor but i also customized it a little bit R.I.P gramps.
the original guitar is not white and i did not use a refrence photo for this model i used the guitar itself as a portrait and i also do not care about how high poly it is so please do not state that. Feedback would be apreciated mainly from some of our veteran players.

item.title: (W.I.P)Custom acoustic guitar(all prims)
item.dc:creator: @the_wanderer The Wanderer
item.description:
@the_wanderer wrote:

Catmark culled means it is subdivided. Means it is smooth unless you have some triangles bunched together. Or if the model isn’t connected at an area, which looks like the problem here. Also can I see a wireframe that isn’t looking at it from an angle so I can actually see the polygon structure? Right now it looks like a jumble of lines.

item.dc:creator: @LordDeth LordDeth
item.description:
@LordDeth wrote:

Even though its been rounded somehow its still bumpy, which makes me believe you don’t know how to align the polys, there’s nothing holding the strings down, there’s no tuning knobs on the head, everything is too rounded off, it looks like its inflatable, the head looks like its a deformed circle. Red background contrasts the blk and white, looks like shit. The list goes on.
